BT /F2 22 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 774 Tm (Qiskit KG Encodings) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 726 Tm (Small User Manual) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 697 Tm (This repository implements a reusable Python pipeline for encoding RDF) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 682 Tm (Knowledge Graphs into quantum states with Qiskit.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 657 Tm (It supports three encoding families:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 632 Tm (- basis encoding) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 615 Tm (- amplitude encoding) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 598 Tm (- phase encoding) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 575 Tm (The default dataset is included in data/running_example.ttl, but the code is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 560 Tm (designed so you can later replace that file with another Turtle graph and run) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 545 Tm (the same pipeline again.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 512 Tm (What The Project Does) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 483 Tm (The workflow is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 458 Tm (1. load an RDF graph from a file) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 439 Tm (2. parse the triples) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 420 Tm (3. build deterministic ID mappings) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 401 Tm (4. create an encoding-specific representation) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 382 Tm (5. build a Qiskit circuit) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 363 Tm (6. simulate locally with Aer) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 344 Tm (7. save logs and figures) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 319 Tm (The code is split into reusable modules under src/:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 294 Tm (- `kg_parser.py`: RDF loading and triple extraction) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 277 Tm (- `id_mapper.py`: entity/object and predicate indexing) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 260 Tm (- `basis_encoding.py`: basis-state encoding of triples) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 243 Tm (- `amplitude_encoding.py`: amplitude vectors over triple indices) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 226 Tm (- `phase_encoding.py`: phase-marking rules over triple indices) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 209 Tm (- `visualization.py`: JSON logs and bar-chart figures) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 192 Tm (- `main.py`: command-line entry point) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 161 Tm (Default Dataset) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 132 Tm (The included example graph contains six triples:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 107 Tm (- Aristotle is typed as Person) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 90 Tm (- Person is a subclass of Mortal) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 73 Tm (- Aristotle lives at Athens) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
