BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 468 Tm (- `--fixed-thesis-mapping`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 451 Tm (- `--weights 2,1,3,1,1,2`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 434 Tm (- `--mark-predicate http://example.org/teaches`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 417 Tm (- `--mark-subject http://example.org/Aristotle`) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 386 Tm (Running The Included Experiments) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 357 Tm (You can also run the thin wrappers in experiments/:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 332 Tm (- `python experiments/exp_basis_running_example.py`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 315 Tm (- `python experiments/exp_amplitude_running_example.py`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 298 Tm (- `python experiments/exp_phase_running_example.py`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 275 Tm (These wrappers call the reusable code in src/ and simply provide default) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 260 Tm (settings for the included thesis example.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 227 Tm (Using Another Turtle File) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 198 Tm (To run the same pipeline on another knowledge graph:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 173 Tm (1. prepare another RDF file in Turtle format) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 154 Tm (2. point the CLI to that file with --input) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 135 Tm (3. optionally pass custom weights or a phase-marking rule) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 110 Tm (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 64 85 Tm (python -m src.main --encoding basis --input path/to/another_graph.ttl) Tj ET
endstream
